---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy-first habit tracking · memoato"
  description="A privacy-first habit tracker with cloud sync, encrypted cloud, and local-only storage modes."
  canonicalPath="/privacy-first"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h1 class="page-title">Privacy-first habit tracking</h1>
      <p class="muted">If it doesn’t feel safe, you won’t log. So we give you options.</p>

      <p>
        memoato supports multiple privacy modes so you can choose the trade-off that fits your life (and still get the
        benefits of a simple timeline and clear progress).
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy modes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cloud sync</strong>: multi-device access with normal server storage.</li>
        <li><strong>Encrypted cloud</strong>: sensitive tracker titles and notes are encrypted client-side before saving.</li>
        <li><strong>Local-only</strong>: data stays on your device (IndexedDB).</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Read the details in the <a href="/privacy">Privacy policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Try it</h2>
      <p>
        If you want “private by default”, start in local-only and switch later if you need multi-device sync.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn primary" href="https://app.memoato.com" rel="noreferrer" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Open app</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/privacy">Privacy policy</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/help">Help & FAQ</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

